  <intervention>
    <intervention_type>Behavioral</intervention_type>
    <intervention_name>Fall Prevention by the Occupational Therapist</intervention_name>
    <description>The interventions included education on adaptive equipment for household activities, adaptive equipment for activities of daily living, proper footwear in all environments, proper body mechanics, position changes, home environment set up, high fall risk activities, safety awareness, low vision and home exercises programs. In addition, discussion and education occurred to improve participation in valued occupations.</description>
    <arm_group_label>Fall Prevention Intervention by OT</arm_group_label>
